<br>
The dangerously radioactive fission byproducts at the centre of the controversy will not even be on Earth since the reactor is not operational until a safe distance above the ground. Nuclear reactions are one million times more powerful than breaking chemical bonds fueling current missions. The advantages for spaceflight applications with such a compact source of energy are impossible to predict in the long run. Faster, longer burns during deep space journeys will vastly increase mission parameters. Assistance during launch phases could eventuate in single stage rockets pushing spacecrafts into orbit meaning far cheaper payloads. <br>
